Australia Newcastle Thermal Coal Falls 1.7% to $129.48 a Ton

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-03-04T12:20:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/australia-newcastle-thermal-coal-falls-1-7-to-129-48-a-ton.html
Power-station coal  prices  at  Australia ’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, fell 1.7 percent
in the week ended today.  Coal prices at the New South Wales port dropped to $129.48
a metric ton from $131.71 the previous week, according to the
 globalCOAL NEWC Index .    Xstrata Plc (XTA) , the world’s largest exporter of power-station
coal,  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  and Rio Tinto Group are among mining
companies that ship coal through Newcastle.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratish Narayanan in Mumbai at 
 pnarayanan9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clyde Russell at 
 crussell7@bloomberg.net  